	Throughout this document, the word 'proof' is used. A proof is a scaled
down representation of an image also known as a 'thumbnail'.


	On-line help is available at all times, simply hold the mouse over the
area of the active window you want help on and press the 'Help' key.


	@{b}Please rate PhotoFolio on Aminet, give it a score out of 10!@{ub}

	To do so, send e-mail to aminet-server@wuarchive.wustl.edu and in the message body put:

	RATE <path> <num>

	Where <path> is the file you want to judge and <num> is a mark from 0..10
with 10 being the best.


Example: RATE gfx/show/PhotoFolio1_2.lha 10


