@{b}@{u}Requirements@{ub}@{uu}

PhotoFolio requires at @{b}minimum@{ub} the following to run:


	· A 68020 based Amiga computer running Kickstart 3.0


	· MUI version 3.8

		Available from @{b}Aminet - util/libs@{ub}


	· Listtree.mcc version 17.53 (included in release)

		Available from @{b}http://home.pages.de/~kmel/@{ub}


	· NList.mcc and NListview.mcc version 19.90

		Available from @{b}Aminet - dev/mui@{ub}


	· jpeg.library version 4.0 (included in release)

		Available from @{b}http://mafeking.scouts.org.au/~paulh@{ub}


	· proof.library version 2.0 (included in release)

		Available from @{b}http://mafeking.scouts.org.au/~paulh@{ub}


	· image.library version 1.0 (included in release)

		Available from @{b}http://mafeking.scouts.org.au/~paulh@{ub}


	·	guigfx.library and render.library

		Available from @{b}Aminet - dev/misc@{ub}


If you have a VLab card:


	·	VLab.mcc version 13.0 (included in release)

		Available from @{b}Aminet - dev/mui@{ub}


If you want to run MysticView:


	·	mysticview.library version 4.1 (included in release)


@{b}@{u}Note:@{ub}@{uu}

	PhotoFolio automatically detects if you have a CyberGraphx card and uses
the native CyberGraphx calls for optimum speed and less memory overhead. If
you don't have a CyberGraphx card then PhotoFolio uses guigfx.library to
render to the screen.
		

@EndNode

