@Node "Main_window" "PhotoFolio.guide/Main_window"
@Prev "Windows"

@Smartwrap

@{u}@{b}Main window@{uu}@{ub}


@{b}Context Menus@{ub}

@{" Listtree Main Menu " Link "Listtree_main_menu" }

@{" Listtree Menu 1    " Link "Listtree_menu_1" }

@{" Listtree Menu 2    " Link "Listtree_menu_2" }

@{" Listtree Menu 3    " Link "Listtree_menu_3" }

@{" Listtree Menu 4    " Link "Listtree_menu_4" }


	PhotoFolio's main window consists of a Listtree.
The Listtree is used to store paths, which you can open into a @{"browse window" Link "Browse_window" }.
These paths should contain images you wish to view or catalogue.


The Listtree has 2 permanent nodes:


@{b}Image Path@{ub} and @{b}Temp Path@{ub}


	Both of these permanent nodes are connected to the "root node", this is
not labeled but it is the far left vertical line connecting the 2 nodes.
Every time you add a path it gets added into the @{b}Image Path@{ub} entry.
Double  clicking  the Image Path will open an ASL requester so you can "Add
one path".


	@{b}Temp Path@{ub} is provided for you to be able to use as a temporary storage
place for paths you have already viewed. To move a path into here, simply
click and drag the path onto the @{b}Temp Path@{ub} entry.

You can also drag paths onto the "root path". Paths that belong to the
"root path" cannot be removed.


	Adding paths, removing paths, indeed any operation on the Listtree is
done by the use of a context menu. Hold down the right button over the
Listtree to access this menu. There are 4 different context menus for the
Listtree and the menu that appears depends on what the mouse is over at the
time the right button was pressed.


	If the mouse was not over any of the Listtree but the window was active you
will get the @{"Listtree Main Menu" Link "Listtree_main_menu" }, which is a standard Amiga menu at the top
of the screen.


	If the mouse was over @{b}Image Path@{ub} or @{b}Temp Path@{ub} and there are entries in the listtree you will get @{"Listtree Menu 1" Link "Listtree_menu_1" }.


	If the mouse was over a path you have already added you will get @{"Listtree Menu 2" Link "Listtree_menu_2" }.


	If the mouse was over a blank area of the Listtree and there are entries
in the listtree you will get @{"Listtree Menu 3" Link "Listtree_menu_3" }.


	If the mouse was over either of the 2 permanent entries or a blank area of
the Listtree and there are no entries in the listtree you will get @{"Listtree Menu 4" Link "Listtree_menu_4" }.


@{i}@{b}Note@{ub}@{ui}

	You can add a path to a @{"browse window" Link "Browse_window" } several ways:


	· Right click on Open in window with the mouse pointer over the path you
wish to display.


	· Double click on the path you wish to display.


	· Drag a path to an already open @{"browse window" Link "Browse_window" }.


Duplicate paths will not be added to the listtree.

@EndNode

@Node "Listtree_main_menu" "PhotoFolio.guide/Listtree_main_menu"
@Next "Listtree_menu_1"
@Prev "Main_window"

@Smartwrap

