@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Make path@{ub}

This will open the @{"make window" Link "Make_window" } allowing you to make proofs of all the
images in the path that the mouse pointer was over.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Make all paths@{ub}

This will open the @{"make window" Link "Make_window" } allowing you to make proofs of all the
images in all the paths in the listtree.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Clear made@{ub}

As each path is made, Photofolio changes the colour of the associated entry
in  the  Listtree  to white. You can tell at a glance which paths have been
made. This menu option changes the path entry back to black.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Re-target path@{ub}

This allows you to re-target all the proofs in the path under the mouse.
This is used if you have moved the location of the original images, after
you have made the proofs. You can use the re-target function to make all
the proofs point to the new location of the images. An ASL requester will
open, select the new path the images reside in and then click OK. The
proofs in the selected path will then be re-targeted to point to the new
location.


@{b}Note:@{ub}

	If the re-targeting routine comes across a non-linked proof, it will be
skipped. @{b}Non-linked proofs cannot be re-targeted@{ub}.
If an image is found it will also be skipped.
@{PARD}


@EndNode

