@Node "History_0.9beta" "PhotoFolio.guide/History_0.9beta"
@Next "History_0.91beta"
@Smartwrap

@{b}@{u}Changes in release 0.9 beta (1/3/1999)@{ub}@{uu}


	· Initial beta release.


@EndNode

@Node "History_0.91beta" "PhotoFolio.guide/History_0.91beta"
@Prev "History_0.9beta"
@Next "History_0.92beta"
@Smartwrap

@{b}@{u}Changes in release 0.91 beta (9/3/1999)@{ub}@{uu}



@{LINDENT 6}
@{b}@{u}Bug Fixes:@{ub}@{uu}

· Fixed a bug where you could not open a project file from non-writeable media. eg: a CD.


· Fixed a bug where the pagination gadgets were not ghosted while a load was taking place.


· Modified the browse load routine to use message ports instead of
PushMethods, this means you can now sucessfully re-size the browse window
while loading.


· Added a few overlooked strings to the catalog file.


· Re-saving already saved non-linked proofs caused an Enforcer hit, now fixed. 


· Fixed a bug where an error could return an incorrect filename.
@{PARD}



@{LINDENT 6}
@{b}@{u}New Features:@{ub}@{uu}

· You can now specify a project file to auto-load on start up. See @{"settings window." Link "Settings_window" }.


· The error window now has context menus. You can delete an individual entry,
clear the whole list or save the error list to a file. See @{"error window." Link "Error_window" }.


· Toggle selected added to @{"Selected Menu" Link "Selected_menu" } and @{"Browse Main Menu" Link "Browse_main_menu" }.


· Error messages are now displayed any of the main libraries could not be opened.


· A save button has been added to the @{"settings window." Link "Settings_window" }.


· The make progress window now opens to a more practical minimum size.


· Added a few more error requesters.
@{PARD}

@EndNode

@Node "History_0.92beta" "PhotoFolio.guide/History_0.92beta"
@Prev "History_0.91beta"
@Next "History_0.93beta"
@Smartwrap

@{b}@{u}Changes in release 0.92 beta (16/3/1999)@{ub}@{uu}



@{LINDENT 6}
@{b}@{u}Bug Fixes:@{ub}@{uu}


· The Save button in the settings window did not work, now fixed.


· Renamed Copy to Copy... in proof menu.


· Renamed Copy selected images to Copy selected images... in selected menu.


· The Listtree project/Image path cycle gadget text in the settings window was bold, now fixed.


· The ASL requester for the Listtree project/Image path setting did not
pass in the file name if Listtree project was selected. Now fixed.


· The sort menu items were not reset when changing pages of proofs, now fixed.


· If Stop was pressed in the browse window while a path was being loaded,
the proofs were not updated correctly. Now fixed.


· An incorrect catalog file was being referenced. Now fixed.


· About requester occasionally crashed PhotoFolio when being closed. Now fixed.


· Due to an oversight, PhotoFolio would not work on 8-bit (256 colour)
CybergraphX screens, this has now been fixed. You @{b}MUST@{ub} however have
guigfx.library installed.


@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
@{b}@{u}New Features:@{ub}@{uu}


· Pressing "space" while showing the last selected image will now exit the show.


· Re-targeting of proofs has now been added. See @{"Proof Menu" Link "Proof_menu" } and @{"Selected Menu" Link "Selected_menu" }.



@{PARD}

@EndNode

@Node "History_0.93beta" "PhotoFolio.guide/History_0.93beta"
@Prev "History_0.92beta"
@Smartwrap

@{b}@{u}Changes in release 0.93 beta (10/05/1999)@{ub}@{uu}



@{LINDENT 6}
@{b}@{u}Bug Fixes:@{ub}@{uu}


· There were several incorrect ASL window titles in the settings menu. Now fixed.


· Opening a project file from a CD or read only device failed. Now fixed.


· I found a minor bug with several of the MUI input handlers. Now fixed.


·  @{b}@{u}Major  Bug  Fix:@{ub}@{uu}  image.library had a problem with the
Picasso  96  picture.datatype,  causing  system  crashes on AGA systems and
non-24 bit images. Now fixed.


· Sometimes when running low on memory the browse window did not update
correctly. Now fixed.


· Closing a browse window while it was loading caused memory loss. Now fixed.


@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
@{b}@{u}New Features:@{ub}@{uu}


· Double clicking a proof will now show it. (User request)


· External viewer support added. (User request)


· VLab card now supported for image grabbing. (VLab.mcc required.)


· Settings window rebuilt.


· Up to 300 proofs (was 50) can now be loaded before displaying them in the
browse window. The browse window is now put to sleep when it is being
updated. (User request)


· Added menu item Project/Save (User request)


· If only one image is shown, pressing 'space' will quit the shower.


· Added error handling if a non-existant path is added to a browse window.


· PhotoFolio's iconified icon is now the same as the program icon.


· Move function now added. (User request)


@{PARD}

@EndNode

@Node "History_1.0" "PhotoFolio.guide/History_1.0"
@Prev "History_0.93beta"
@Smartwrap

@{b}@{u}Changes in release 1.0 (29/05/1999)@{ub}@{uu}



@{LINDENT 6}
@{b}@{u}Bug Fixes:@{ub}@{uu}

· @{b}@{u}Major  Bug  Fix:@{ub}@{uu} Aborting loading of proofs by closing the browse window under certain conditions
during a load caused PhotoFolio to crash. Now fixed.


· @{b}@{u}Major  Bug  Fix:@{ub}@{uu} Stopping loading of proofs by pressing Stop under certain conditions caused PhotoFolio to
deadlock. Now fixed.


· @{b}@{u}Major  Bug  Fix:@{ub}@{uu} Pausing loading of proofs under certain conditions caused PhotoFolio to
deadlock. Now fixed.


· @{b}@{u}Major  Bug  Fix:@{ub}@{uu} Shutting down PhotoFolio while loading proofs under certain conditions caused PhotoFolio to
deadlock. Now fixed.


· When  using  a non-CyberGraphX screen and the internal viewer, greyscale
images did not display correctly. Now fixed.


@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
@{b}@{u}New Features:@{ub}@{uu}


· @{"MysticView" Link "MysticView" } by Timm S. Müller is now fully supported internally. See @{"MysticView window" Link "MysticView_window" }.


· Browse windows can now ignore icon (.info) files. See @{"settings window" Link "Settings_window" }.


· Improved documentation explaining the owner/group/category concept.


@{PARD}

@EndNode

@Node "History_1.1" "PhotoFolio.guide/History_1.1"
@Prev "History_1.0"
@Smartwrap

@{b}@{u}Changes in release 1.1 (11/06/1999)@{ub}@{uu}



@{LINDENT 6}
@{b}@{u}Bug Fixes:@{ub}@{uu}

· VLab - If you quick grabbed and then closed the window, the list was not
freed causing amnesia - Now fixed.


· If you were showing selected images, then deleted the "next" or
"previous" image before it had be viewed, PhotoFolio would freeze. Now
Fixed.


· Under certain conditions some context menu items were disabled, however
their main menu equivalents, weren't. Now fixed.


· When creating a proof of a greyscale image that was smaller than the
required proof size, the proof displayed contained garbage. Now fixed.


· When using the akPNG datatype to load a PNG image, the system would hang
because of the large amount of stack space required by the akPNG datatype.
Now fixed.


· If a proof was flagged as questionable and it was selected, but hidden,
the "selected" operations still worked on it. Now fixed.


· Sometimes a image path that was added to the listtree was not fully
qualified, but instead, referenced from PROGDIR:, this path was then stored
in the proof. If you then moved PhotoFolio to a different place on your
hard disk, the path stored in these proofs became invalid, meaning
PhotoFolio could not find the original image associated with the proof.
PhotoFolio now fully qualifies every path. Now fixed


· If you iconifed while a browse window was loading, PhotoFolio would
crash. Now fixed.


· Some ASL requesters opened on an incorrect screen. Now fixed.


· Since changing how the browse window loaded proofs, a bug appeared where
the low memory check only happened when the proofs were added to the
window. This didn't take into account the memory required to actually
display the proof. Now fixed.


· "Apply all" in the change attributes requester stopped working.
Now fixed.


· Selecting or de-selecting all proofs caused double update of the browse
window. Now fixed.


· Library detection on start-up failed under certain conditions. Now fixed.
guigfx.library AND render.library are now required even if you are running
CyberGraphX.


· If when moving an image you said no to replace a file with the same name,
PhotoFolio still deleted the source image. Now fixed.


· VLab - If vlab.mcc was installed but you didn't have vlab.library, PhotoFolio
would crash. Now fixed.


· Sorting alphabetically now treats uppercase the same as lowercase.


· Removing a path from the main window with no path selected, caused enforcer hits/crashes.
Now fixed.


· Making paths with names greater than 32 characters in length used to cause truncated names
to appear in the listtree (with display Full Paths selected). Now fixed.


· Dropping a path from the listtree onto the browse window, did not reset
the sort menu items. Now fixed.


· Saving the default project opened an ASL requester, it shouldn't have. Now fixed.


@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
@{b}@{u}New Features:@{ub}@{uu}


· Added the option to turn automatic opening of the @{"error window" Link "Error_window" }
 on or off. See @{"settings window" Link "Settings_window"}.


· In earlier versions, paths containing no files were not added to the list
tree, now they are.


· Added FAQ and Getting started to the documentation.


· The way PhotoFolio ignores .info files in the browse window has been
changed. You can now enter a Amiga DOS pattern to ignore any sorts of
file types.


· PhotoFolio currently stores proofs in a directory structure that mirrors
the image's. I have added a check box to turn this on and off in
"Settings/Make", allowing PhotoFolio to store the proofs directly into the
directory specified.


· Double clicking the "Image path" will now open an ASL requester so you
can "Add one path"


· The move window now remembers the last move's paths


· Move now recognises the "Proof load display update" setting and will
update the browse window(s) accordingly. This will speed up the move
operation.


· Added the link status in the proof information window.


· Browse windows menus have been slightly rearranged.


@{PARD}

@EndNode

@Node "History_1.2" "PhotoFolio.guide/History_1.2"
@Prev "History_1.1"
@Smartwrap

@{b}@{u}Changes in release 1.2 (04/10/1999)@{ub}@{uu}



@{LINDENT 6}
@{b}@{u}Bug Fixes:@{ub}@{uu}


· Project ASL requesters always opened on the workbench. Now Fixed.


@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
@{b}@{u}New Features:@{ub}@{uu}


· The current project file name has been added to the main window title bar.


· Added '0' to the show window for auto size.


· Added numeric keypad input for the show window.


@{PARD}

@EndNode

@Node "Attribute_object" "PhotoFolio.guide/Attribute_object"
@Next "Group_menu"
@Prev "Windows"

@Smartwrap

@{b}@{u}Attribute Object@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}Context Menus@{ub}

@{" Group Menu    " Link "Group_menu" }

@{" Category Menu " Link "Category_menu" }


	This is the @{"browse window's" Link "Browse_window" } attribute object.
Using this object you can determine which proofs are displayed, dependent
on the attributes you have selected.


	At the top of the window is a text string describing the current owner. This
owner can be changed with the "Change owner" item in either @{"group menu" Link "Group_menu" } or
@{"category menu" Link "Category_menu" }.


	Below the owner string is a cycle gadget, this allows you to change
between the 4 groups. You can change or enter new group names using
the "New group name" item in @{"group menu" Link "Group_menu" }. 


	Below the group cycle gadget is the categories list. This contains the
list of 22 categories for the current group. You can select, de-select, add
new categories, save the owner settings, delete a single entry or delete
all entries by using @{"category menu" Link "Category_menu" }.


	Below the category object is a cycle gadget containing the match criteria
for the selected categories. The choices are as follows:


Match any proof that:


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Is Exactly This@{ub}

This means that for a proof to be displayed, its attributes must match
@{b}EXACTLY@{ub} with the selected categories.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Contains All Selected@{ub}

This means that for a proof to be displayed, its attributes must contain
the selected categories.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Contains Any One@{ub}

This means that for a proof to be displayed, its attributes must contain
any one of the selected categories.
@{PARD}


	Below the match criteria cycle gadget are two buttons. The
@{b}Update@{ub} button is used to update the proofs displayed, dependent on
the match criteria you have selected. The @{b}All@{ub} button simply
displays all proofs regardless of the match criteria.

@EndNode

@Node "Group_menu" "PhotoFolio.guide/Group_menu"
@Next "Category_menu"
@Prev "Attribute_object"

@Smartwrap

@{u}@{b}Attribute Group Menu@{uu}@{ub}


	This menu is accessed by right clicking on the group cycle gadget.


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}New group name@{ub}

This brings up the @{"new group window" Link "New_group_window"} 
which allows you to enter new group names or modify existing names.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Change owner@{ub}

This brings up the @{"change owner window" Link "Change_Owner_window"} 
which allows you to change the current owner.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Save owner settings@{ub}

This brings up the @{"save owner window" Link "Save_Owner_window"} 
which allows you to save the current settings into an owner.
@{PARD}

@EndNode

@Node "Category_menu" "PhotoFolio.guide/Category_menu"
@Prev "Group_menu"

@Smartwrap

@{u}@{b}Attribute Category Menu@{uu}@{ub}


	This menu is accessed by right clicking on the category list.


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Select all@{ub}

This selects all the categories currently in the list.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}De-select all@{ub}

This de-selects all the categories currently in the list.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
This brings up the @{"new category window" Link "New_category_window"} 
which allows you to add new categories
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Change owner@{ub}

This brings up the @{"change owner window" Link "Change_Owner_window"} 
which allows you to change the current owner.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Save owner settings@{ub}

This brings up the @{"save owner window" Link "Save_Owner_window"} 
which allows you to save the current settings into an owner.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Delete entry@{ub}

This deletes the category entry currently under the mouse.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Delete all entries@{ub}

This deletes all the category entries in the list.
@{PARD}

@EndNode

@Node "Proof_group_object" "PhotoFolio.guide/Proof_group_object"
@Next "Selected_menu"
@Prev "Windows"

@Smartwrap

@{b}@{u}Proof Group Object@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}Context Menus@{ub}

@{" Selected Menu    " Link "Selected_menu" }


	This is where the @{"browse window" Link "Browse_window" } adds proofs.
Each time a proof is loaded it gets added to this group, you can scroll
through the proofs, and display them while loading is in process.

@EndNode

@Node "Selected_menu" "PhotoFolio.guide/Selected_menu"
@Prev "Proof_group_object"

@Smartwrap

@{u}@{b}Selected Menu@{uu}@{ub}


	This menu is accessed by right clicking in the proof group object in an
area not used by proofs.


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Select all@{ub}

This selects all the proofs currently displayed.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}De-select all@{ub}

This de-selects all the proofs currently displayed.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Togle selected@{ub}

This toggles all the selected proofs to de-selected and vice versa.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Show selected@{ub}

This shows all the currently selected proofs in the @{"show window" Link "Show_window"}.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Copy selected@{ub}

This copies all the images associated with the proofs to a new path.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Correct selected gamma@{ub}

This applies auto gamma correction to the selected proofs.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Change selected attributes@{ub}

This opens the @{"change attributes window" Link "Change_attributes_window"} and allows you to change
the attributes of the currently selected proofs.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Save selected@{ub}

This allows you to save the selected proofs. If you don't want to @{"make" Link "Make_window"} a
directory of proofs, you can load the images direct into the @{"browse window" Link "Browse_window" } 
and then just save the proofs you want.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Re-target selected@{ub}

This allows you to re-target the selected proofs. This is used if you have
moved the location of the original images, after you have made the proofs.
You can use the re-target function to make all the selected proofs point to
the new location of the images. An ASL requester will open, select the new
path the images reside in and then click OK. The selected proofs will then
be re-targeted to point to the new location.


@{b}Note:@{ub}

	If the re-targeting routine comes across a non-linked proof, it will be
skipped. @{b}Non-linked proofs cannot be re-targeted@{ub}.


If a non-saved proof is found, and the settings are set to linked, then the
proof will be saved using the re-targeted path. If the settings are set to
non-linked, then the proof will be skipped and it won't be saved or re-targeted.


(If a proof's top line of text is @{b}NOT BOLD@{ub} then the proof is non-saved. If
the top line of text @{b}IS BOLD@{ub} the the proof has been saved.)
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Delete selected@{ub}

This deletes the selected proofs and the images associated with them.
@{PARD}


@EndNode

@Node "Proof_menu" "PhotoFolio.guide/Proof_menu"
@Prev "Browse_window"
@Next "Selected_menu"

@Smartwrap

@{u}@{b}Proof Menu@{uu}@{ub}


	This menu is accessed by right clicking on a proof.


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Information@{ub}

This gives information on the proof currently under the mouse.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Show@{ub}

This shows the proof currently under the mouse in the @{"show window" Link "Show_window"}.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Copy@{ub}

This copies the proof currently under the mouse to a new path.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Move@{ub}

This moves a proof and/or its associated image to another location on disk.

When selecting move, a @{"move window" Link "Move_window"} will open, using this you can select
where you want to move the proofs/images to.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Correct gamma@{ub}

This applies auto gamma correction to the proof currently under the mouse.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Change attributes@{ub}

This opens the @{"change attributes window" Link "Change_attributes_window"} and allows you to change
the attributes of the proof currently under the mouse.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Save proof@{ub}

This allows you to save the proof currently under the mouse. If you don't want to @{"make" Link "Make_window"} a
directory of proofs, you can load the images direct into the @{"browse window" Link "Browse_window" } 
and then just save the proofs you want.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Re-target proof@{ub}

This allows you to re-target the proof under the mouse. This is used if you
have moved the location of the original image, after you have made the
proof. You can use the re-target function to make the proof point to the
new location of the image. An ASL requester will open, select the new path
the image resides in and then click OK. The proof will then be re-targeted
to point to the new location.


@{b}Note:@{ub}

@{b}Non-linked proofs cannot be re-targeted@{ub}.

If you are re-targeting a non-saved proof, and the settings are set to linked, then the
proof will be saved using the re-targeted path. If the settings are set to
non-linked, you will get an error requester.

(If a proof's top line of text is @{b}NOT BOLD@{ub} then the proof is non-saved. If
the top line of text @{b}IS BOLD@{ub} the the proof has been saved.)
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Delete@{ub}

This deletes the proof currently under the mouse and the image associated with it.
@{PARD}


@EndNode

