@Node "Change_attributes_window" "PhotoFolio.guide/Change_attributes_window"
@Next "Group_menu"
@Prev "Windows"

@Smartwrap

@{b}@{u}Change Attributes Window@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}Context Menus@{ub}

@{" Group Menu      " Link "Group_menu" }

@{" Category Menu   " Link "Category_menu" }

@{" Show Image Menu " Link "Show_image_menu" }


	The change attributes window is used to modify the attributes of one or
more proofs.


	On the left hand side of the window is the attribute selection area. On
the right is the proof display area which displays a copy of the proof whos
attributes you want to change, as well as some selection boxes.


@{b}@{u}Overview@{ub}@{uu}

A powerful and comprehensive cataloguing system is included in PhotoFolio.


Each proof can be catalogued into 1 of 255 owners, 1 of 4 groups and any
one or all of 22 categories.


@{b}@{u}Owner@{ub}@{uu}

This was introduced so that you could look at your friends images, using
their categories, and groups, without modifying your existing setup.


If for example you allocated yourself owner 10 and your friend had owner
11, you could copy his owner file (PROGDIR:owners/11.owner) into your
PROGDIR:owners/ directory and then view his images using his categories and
groups. Of course, if you have a lot of images and you run out of
groups/categories, there is nothing stopping you using more than one owner
for yourself, you might allocate 1-20 for yourself and 21-40 for your
friend etc up to 255.


@{b}@{u}Group@{ub}@{uu}

Think of group as a 'heading'. For example, "Textures", "Renders",
"Watercolours", "Backgrounds" etc.


@{b}@{u}Category@{ub}@{uu}

Think of category as a 'classification'. For example, "Stone", "Water",
"Clouds", "Metal" etc.


For example:

Let us assume you have allocated yourself owner 10 and you want to
catalogue a directory on your disk devoted to textures, for a 3D rendering
package. These image textures may include, a frog, the moon, marble, a eucalyptus tree,
some oranges, a ladies face, etc.


Firstly you would name a group called "Textures", then create some
categories inside that group called, "Animals", "Stone", "Nature", "Food",
"Human", "Space", "Backgrounds".


You can now assign the frog image to "Animals" @{b}AND@{ub} "Nature"
@{b}AND@{ub} "Backgrounds".


The moon image to "Space" @{b}AND@{ub} "Backgrounds".


The marble to "Stone" @{b}AND@{ub} "Backgrounds".


Eucalyptus tree to "Nature".


The oranges to "Food".


And the ladies face to "Human".


In the @{"browse window" Link "Browse_window" }, you can now view these proofs by their categories.


@{b}@{u}Attribute Selection Area@{ub}@{uu}

	At the top is a text string describing the current owner. This owner can
be changed with the "Change owner" item in either @{"group menu" Link "Group_menu" } or
@{"category menu" Link "Category_menu" }.


	Below the owner string is a cycle gadget, this allows you to change
between the 4 groups. You can change or enter new group names using
the "New group name" item in @{"group menu" Link "Group_menu" }. 


	Below the group cycle gadget is the categories list. This contains the
list of 22 categories for the current group. You can select, de-select, add
new categories, save the owner settings, delete a single entry or delete
all entries by using @{"category menu" Link "Category_menu" }.


	Below the categories list is a proof comment text string. Here you can
add a comment about the image.


	Below the proof comment is check box labelled "questionable". This can be
used to flag the content of an image. Any images with this flag set can be
hidden from a @{"browse window" Link "Browse_window" } using the Hide Questionable
menu item.


@{b}@{u}Proof Display Area@{ub}@{uu}

	Displayed here is a copy of the proof whos attributes you are changing.
Right clicking on this proof brings up the @{"show image menu" Link "Show_image_menu" }.


	Below the proof are 4 check boxes, these allow you to selectively change
only certain attributes of a proof. Let's say you have already set the
attributes of 200 or so proofs, but forgot to add a comment. You can now
re-select the proofs, turn off all the check boxes except proof comment, type
in your comment and then "apply all". Photofolio will then go through and
only change the proof comment leaving all the other attributes in tact.


@{b}@{u}Changing Attributes@{ub}@{uu}

	Below both of the above groups is a lock settings check box. This will
lock the currently set attributes in the window. With this off, the proof
being displayed will copy its existing attributes to the attribute
selection area. However turning lock settings on will prevent this from
happening.

	This is handy if you want to change proof attribute one at a time, but
don't want to have to keep re-selecting your attributes.


	There are 4 buttons at the bottom of the window:


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Skip@{ub}

This skips the current proof, without changing any attributes.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Apply@{ub}

This applies the current attributes to this proof only.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Apply all@{ub}

This applies the current attributes to all the selected proofs.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Cancel@{ub}

This aborts changing attributes and closes the window.
@{PARD}


	To change a proofs attributes, simply select the owner, then the group,
then the category or categories (shift click), type in your comment, and
check questionable if required.

	Now select which attributes you want to apply, using the check boxes below
the proof and then use the "apply" button or the "apply all" button.

@EndNode

@Node "Show_image_menu" "PhotoFolio.guide/Show_image_menu"
@Prev "Change_attributes_window"

@Smartwrap

@{u}@{b}Show Image Menu@{uu}@{ub}


	This menu is accessed by right clicking on the proof object in the change
attribute window.


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Show image@{ub}

This will show the current displayed proof's image in the @{"show window" Link "Show_window"}.
@{PARD}

@EndNode

@Node "Change_owner_window" "PhotoFolio.guide/Change_owner_window"
@Prev "Change_attributes_window"

@Smartwrap

@{b}@{u}Change Owner Window@{ub}@{uu}


	The change owner window is used to select the new owner that you want to
change to.


	The window contains a slider and two buttons, @{b}Ok@{ub} and
@{b}Set@{ub}. Use the slider to select the owner number you want then click
@{b}Ok@{ub}. The owner will then be changed. You can click @{b}Set@{ub} 
instead of @{b}Ok@{ub}, in this case the window will stay open but the
owner will change. You can use this to look through your owners quickly.


	To abort an owner change just close the window.

@EndNode

@Node "New_group_window" "PhotoFolio.guide/New_group_window"
@Prev "Change_attributes_window"

@Smartwrap

@{b}@{u}New Group Window@{ub}@{uu}


	The new group window is used to change or enter new group names which
appear in the cycle gadget.


	The window contains 4 string gadgets, 1 for each group, and 2 buttons,
@{b}Ok@{ub} and @{b}Cancel@{ub}. Simply type in your new group names and
press @{b}Ok@{ub}.


	To abort an new group just close the window or click @{b}Cancel@{ub}.

@EndNode

@Node "New_category_window" "PhotoFolio.guide/New_category_window"
@Prev "Change_attributes_window"

@Smartwrap

@{b}@{u}New Category Window@{ub}@{uu}


	The new category window is used to enter new category names into the
category list.


	The window contains a string gadget, and 2 buttons, @{b}Add name@{ub} and
@{b}Close@{ub}. Simply type in your new category name and click @{b}Add
name@{ub}. The window will stay open so you can keep entering new
categories, when you are finished click @{b}Close@{ub} or close the window.


	A maximum of 22 categories is allowed.

@EndNode

@Node "Save_owner_window" "PhotoFolio.guide/Save_owner_window"
@Prev "Change_attributes_window"

@Smartwrap

@{b}@{u}Save Owner Window@{ub}@{uu}


	The save owner window is used to save newly modified owners.


	The window contains a slider, a string gadget and two buttons, @{b}Ok@{ub} and
@{b}Cancel@{ub}. Use the slider to select the owner number you want to save as,
enter a string into the identification gadget, such as your name, then
click @{b}Ok@{ub}. The new owner will then be saved. You will be warned if
the new owner already exists. 


	To abort an owner save just close the window or click on @{b}Cancel@{ub}.


@EndNode

@Node "About_window" "PhotoFolio.guide/About_window"
@Prev "Windows"

@Smartwrap

@{b}@{u}About Window@{ub}@{uu}


	This  window  gives  you  general information about Photofolio as well as
contact addresses for the authors.

@EndNode

@Node "Make_window" "PhotoFolio.guide/Make_window"
@Prev "Windows"

@Smartwrap

@{b}@{u}Make Window@{ub}@{uu}


	The make window is used to make a directory of proofs without displaying
them. This has the advantage of being slightly quicker. It is made up of 2
pages.  As  each path in the @{"listtree" Link "Main_window"} is made Photofolio changes its colour
to white to make it easy to see which paths have and haven't been made.


	The @{b}Start@{ub} button at the bottom of the window will start the make
process.


@{b}@{u}Page 1: Make@{ub}@{uu}

	This page of settings determines how the proofs will be made.


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Proof size@{ub}

This sets the width x height of the proofs being made.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Proof save JPEG quality@{ub}

Each proof is saved internally as a jpeg image. This setting determines
the quality of the proof.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Proof destination directory@{ub}

This is the directory PhotoFolio will use when making proofs. A directory
structure mirroring the original image will be created here. This path is
only valid if the proofs are linked.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Proof linking@{ub}

PhotoFolio can store proofs in 2 different ways, linked and non-linked.


	A linked proof is stored in a totally different place to that of the
original image. It is stored inside the proof destination path (above), in
a directory structure that mirrors the original image.


	A non-linked proof is stored with the original image. The file name is
changed so that the two files can co-exist in the same directory. Only the
extender is changed so it is easy to pick a proof from a real image.
@{PARD}


	@{b}Make general settings@{ub}


@{LINDENT 12}
		@{b}Quality scaling (slow)@{ub}

You have a choice of 3 different scaling routines when PhotoFolio scales
the original image to the proof size.

	1:	Low quality scaling (fast)

	2:	High quality scaling (slow)

	3:	Cubic interpolation scaling (VERY slow)

If quality scaling (slow) is checked, then the high quality scaling will be
used. This will unghost cubic interpolation scaling to allow you to check it
if you wish. Please note that low quality scaling is still pretty good, and
is @{b}MUCH@{ub} faster than the other two methods.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 12}
		@{b}Cubic scaling (slower)@{ub}

This enables the cubic interpolation on the scaling. It's very slow.	
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 12}
		@{b}Count files before making@{ub}

With this checked, PhotoFolio will scan the directory and count the files.
This enables PhotoFolio to update progress indicators while the make is in
progress. If this is not checked, no progress indicators will be displayed.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 12}
		@{b}Add path to list after make@{ub}

Once the path has been made. The new proof path (if linked) is
automatically added to @{b}Temp Path@{ub}. This will avoid confusion if
abbreviated names is turned on for the listtree.
@{PARD}


@{b}@{u}Page 2: Attributes@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}Context Menus@{ub}

@{" Group Menu      " Link "Group_menu" }

@{" Category Menu   " Link "Category_menu" }


	This page allows you to set the attributes each proof will be given
during the make process. Its like having a default setting for all the
proofs.


	At the top is a text string describing the current owner. This owner can
be changed with the "Change owner" item in either @{"group menu" Link "Group_menu" } or
@{"category menu" Link "Category_menu" }.


	Below the owner string is a cycle gadget, this allows you to change
between the 4 groups. You can change or enter new group names using
the "New group name" item in @{"group menu" Link "Group_menu" }. 


	Below the group cycle gadget is the categories list. This contains the
list of 22 categories for the current group. You can select, de-select, add
new categories, save the owner settings, delete a single entry or delete
all entries by using @{"category menu" Link "Category_menu" }.


	Below the categories list is a proof comment text string. Here you can
add a comment about the image.


	Below the proof comment is check box labelled "questionable". This can be
used to flag the content of an image. Any images with this flag set can be
hidden from a @{"browse window" Link "Browse_window" } using the Hide Questionable
menu item.


@EndNode

@Node "Settings_window" "PhotoFolio.guide/Settings_window"
@Prev "Windows"

@Smartwrap

@{b}@{u}Settings Window@{ub}@{uu}


	The settings window is used to set the user preferences for PhotoFolio. It
is made up of 8 pages.


	It has 4 buttons at the bottom of the window:


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Ok@{ub}

This accepts all the settings and closes the window. Any display updates
that are needed are then made.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Apply@{ub}

This is the same as @{b}Ok@{ub}, however the window stays open.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Save@{ub}

This accepts all the settings and saves the current settings to disk as the
default settings.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Cancel@{ub}

This cancels any changes and closes the window.
@{PARD}



@{b}@{u}Page 1: Make@{ub}@{uu}

	This page of settings determines how the proofs will be made.


@{b}@{i}Make defaults@{ub}@{ui}

@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Proof size@{ub}

This sets the width x height of the proofs being made.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Proof save JPEG quality@{ub}

Each proof is saved internally as a jpeg image. This setting determines
the quality of the proof.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Quality scaling (slow)@{ub}

You have a choice of 3 different scaling routines when PhotoFolio scales
the original image to the proof size.

	1:	Low quality scaling (fast)

	2:	High quality scaling (slow)

	3:	Cubic interpolation scaling (slowest)

Please note that low quality scaling is still pretty good, and is
@{b}MUCH@{ub} faster than the other two methods.

This can be changed from the @{"browse window's" Link "Browse_window" } @{"menu" Link "Browse_main_menu" }.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Proof linking@{ub}

PhotoFolio can store proofs in 2 different ways, linked and non-linked.


	A linked proof is stored in a totally different place to that of the
original image. It is stored inside the proof destination path (above), in
a directory structure that mirrors the original image.


	A non-linked proof is stored with the original image. The file name is
changed so that the two files can co-exist in the same directory. Only the
extender is changed so it is easy to pick a proof from a real image.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Proof destination directory@{ub}

This is the directory PhotoFolio will use when making proofs. This path is
only valid if the proofs are linked.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Mirror image directory structure@{ub}

When proofs are saved they can be saved directly into the "Proof
destination directory" or, if this option is checked, into a directory
structure which mirrors that of the original image. For example:


Your image is stored in: @{b}Graphics:images/pictures/jpegs@{ub}


Your Proof destination directory is: @{b}Ram:proofs@{ub}


Then without this checked, the proofs will be saved into @{b}Ram:proofs.@{ub}


With this checked the proofs will be saved into @{b}Ram:proofs/graphics/images/pictures/jpegs@{ub}


This is great for creating CDs of images where your proof structure matches
that of your original images.
@{PARD}


@{b}@{i}Miscellaneous@{ub}@{ui}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Count files before making@{ub}

With this checked, PhotoFolio will scan the directory and count the files.
This enables PhotoFolio to update progress indicators while the make is in
progress. If this is not checked, no progress indicators will be displayed.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Add path to list after make@{ub}

Once the path has been made. The new proof path (if linked) is
automatically added to @{b}Temp Path@{ub}. This will avoid confusion if
abbreviated names is turned on for the listtree.
@{PARD}


@{b}@{u}Page 2: Proofs@{ub}@{uu}


	This page allows you to change the way the proofs appear in the @{"browse window" Link "Browse_window" }.


@{b}@{i}Proof Display@{ub}@{ui}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Description position@{ub}

This sets where the proof text appears with the proof. It can be placed in
6 different positions:

	1:	No Text

	2:	Text Left

	3:	Text Right

	4:	Text Top

	5:	Text Bottom

	6:	Bubble

No Text turns text off altogether. Bubble means that no text will be
visible, however if you hold the mouse still over a proof, the text will
appear in a bubble.

@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Proof text attributes@{ub}

By checking (or not checking) each of the three boxes, you can turn the
different lines of text associated with the proof on or off.
@{PARD}


@{b}@{i}guigfx.library@{ub}@{ui}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Proof dithering@{ub}

@{b}@{u}Note:@{ub}@{uu}
 This is only available if you are using guigfx.library.


This cycle gadget allows you to change between 4 different modes of dithering:

	1.	None

	2.	Floyd-Steinberg

	3.	Random

	4.	EDD

This setting is for the proofs only. If you find your system is slow, turn
this off and the graphics will speed up, however the quality of the proofs
will suffer.
@{PARD}


@{b}@{u}Page 3: Browse@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}@{i}Display modes@{ub}@{ui}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Proof sorting@{ub}

Proofs can be sorted in 4 ways:

	1:	No Sort

	2:	Sort alphabetically

	3:	Sort by size

	4:	Sort by type

Setting this cycle gadget to one of these modes, means that @{b}AFTER@{ub} 
a load is finished, the proofs will be automatically sorted.

This can be changed from the @{"browse window's" Link "Browse_window" } @{"menu" Link "Browse_main_menu" }.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Hide questionable@{ub}

Checking this means that any proof that has this attribute set, will be
hidden from the @{"browse window" Link "Browse_window" }.

This can be changed from the @{"browse window's" Link "Browse_window" } @{"menu" Link "Browse_main_menu" }.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Attributes panel@{ub}

This toggles the attributes panel in the @{"browse window" Link "Browse_window" } on or off.
@{PARD}


@{b}@{i}Owner@{ub}@{ui}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Default owner@{ub}

This sets the default owner.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Lock owner number@{ub}

If this is checked, when you open a @{"change attributes window" Link "Change_attributes_window"}, the
lock settings check box will also be checked. This will probably be removed
in the final release.
@{PARD}


@{b}@{i}Miscellaneous@{ub}@{ui}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Proof load display update@{ub}

Every time an object is added to a virtual group, MUI updates the entire
virtual group. This makes adding proofs to a @{"browse window" Link"Browse_window" } very slow.
To try and speed things up, I have added this setting. You can set this to
anything between 1 and 300. The default is 5. This means, that the display
will update every 5 proofs.

That is if you are loading a directory with 30 proofs, you will not see
anything until the first 5 are loaded, and then again after the 10th is
loaded etc...
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Confirm closing browse windows@{ub}

If this is checked, a confirmation requester will appear whenever you close a @{"browse window" Link "Browse_window" }.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Ignore files matching this pattern:@{ub}

This string gadget can be used to tell the browse window to ignore any
files that match this pattern.

For example to ignore .info files you should enter #?.info into this gadget.
@{PARD}


@{b}@{u}Page 4: Show@{ub}@{uu}


Show has 3 pages. One for PhotoFolio's internal viewer and one for MysticView.


At  the  top  of  the Show Page is a cycle gadget that allows you to select
the image viewerPhotoFolio uses.


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Default image viewer@{ub}


@{b}Internal@{ub}

	Use PhotoFolio's internal viewer to view the images.


@{b}External@{ub}

	Use an external viewer to view images. eg: CyberShow


@{b}MysticView@{ub}

	Use MysticView to view the images.

@{PARD}


	@{b}@{u}Page 1: Internal@{ub}@{uu}


@{LINDENT 6}
		@{b}Progressive image loading@{ub}

		With this turned on, the image being displayed in the show window will be
seen as it is being loaded. Otherwise the image won't be seen until the
load is complete.

		@{b}@{i}Note@{ub}@{ui} This feature is not available with datatype loading.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
			@{b}Scaled image loading@{ub}

		With this turned on, the image being displayed will automatically be scaled
to fit the screen as it is loaded.
@{PARD}


	@{b}@{u}Page 2: External@{ub}@{uu}


@{LINDENT 6}
			@{b}External viewer@{ub}

		This string gadget allows you to enter the path:filename of the external
program to use if External viewer is selected.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
			@{b}External viewer arguments@{ub}

		This allows you to enter the arguments you wish to pass to the external
viewing program. When calling the external viewer, PhotoFolio builds an
argument string in this manner:

		1) The name of external viewing program.

		2) The argument string is then appended to this.

		3) Any files to be viewed are then appended to this.


		@{b}@{u}Note:@{ub}@{uu}

			The Amiga limits the length of any argument strings. Consequently, if the
number of files appended to the argument string exceeds this limit, the
string will be truncated and you won't see all the selected files.

@{PARD}


			@{b}@{i}guigfx.library@{ub}@{ui}


@{LINDENT 6}
			@{b}Show dithering@{ub}

		@{b}@{u}Note:@{ub}@{uu}
		 This is only available if you are using guigfx.library.


		This cycle gadget allows you to change between 4 different modes of dithering:

		1.	None

		2.	Floyd-Steinberg

		3.	Random

		4.	EDD

		This setting is for the showing of images only. If you find your system is
slow,  turn this off and the graphics will speed up, however the quality of
the shown images will suffer.
@{PARD}


	@{b}@{u}Page 3: MysticView@{ub}@{uu}


@{LINDENT 6}
			@{b}Show buttons@{ub}

		This turns the button bar in the top of the MysticView window on and off.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
			@{b}Show picture info@{ub}

		This turns the picture information bar in the bottom of the MysticView
window on and off. It displays the image file name and the size of the
image (width x height).
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
			@{b}Show arrows@{ub}

		When enabled, draw arrows at the picture's borders, when it is not fully
visible in the respective direction.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
			@{b}Show PIP@{ub}

		This displays a thumbnail of the image in the top left hand corner of the
image. It contains a green box which indicates the visible portion of the
image.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
			@{b}Show cursor@{ub}

		This setting will activate a tiny crosshair on the picture, indicating the
current cursor position. scrolling will move the cursor, and zooming will
go to that destination.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
			@{b}Mouse drag image@{ub}

		This enable scrolling of an image by clicking the left button and dragging
the mouse.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
			@{b}Use static palette@{ub}

		This option will cause MysticView to use a static palette instead of a
dynamic one (being calculated for each picture). This option is meaningless
on hicolor and truecolor displays.
 
		Static palette versus dynamic palettes: 


		A static palette,

		· gives bad results without dithering.

		· produces more stable quality with dithering.

		· will trigger MysticView's automatic dithering in most cases.

		· causes less flickering when you advance from one picture to another, because there is no need to clear the display.

		· is not necessarily faster than a dynamic one. This depends on the picture.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
			@{b}Window display mode@{ub}


			@{b}Scale with Aspect@{ub}

				Scale with Aspect means that the image is scaled to fit the window size,
maintaining its aspect ratio. If the window is re-sized, the image will
also be re-sized.This mode guarantees that the image is always fully
visible.


			@{b}Display 1:1 Pixel@{ub}

				Display 1:1 Pixel means the image is displayed actual size, regardless of
the window size. Represent each pixel in the image by one pixel on the
screen.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
			@{b}Refresh mode@{ub}


			@{b}No realtime refresh@{ub}

				No realtime update takes place. the image will be rendered in
highest quality.


			@{b}Grid refresh@{ub}

				A 10x10 grid is drawn instead of the picture, then the picture is
rendered into this grid with highest quality.


			@{b}Opaque refresh@{ub}

				This option enables MysticView's opaque window update with the full
window contents. after a quick and dirty preview has been displayed, the
image is rendered into the display in highest quality (if necessary). This
option increases memory consumption dramatically and should be enabled only
on systems with a fast CPU.

@{PARD}


@{b}@{u}Page 5: Scanners@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}VLab@{ub}


@{b}@{i}Save@{ub}@{ui}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}VLab save filename@{ub}

This allows you to enter the default name to use when saving VLab image
grabs. The filename should consist of text characters followed by a 3 digit
number. EG: Graphics:VLab/Grabs/VLabGrab000.

PhotoFolio will automatically increment the number on the end of the
filename each time a grab is saved. This way you can batch save grabs, and
they will each have their own unique filename.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}VLab save JPeg quality@{ub}

This determines the quality of the saved VLab JPeg.
@{PARD}


@{b}@{u}Page 6: Other@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}@{i}Listtree@{ub}@{ui}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Abbreviated/full paths@{ub}

This sets the way the paths are displayed in the @{"main window's" Link "Main_window"} listtree.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Default path@{ub}

This cycle gadget has 2 options:

	1. Listtree project

	2. Image path

Using this, you can have either and image path or a Listtree project
automatically load on program start-up. If you load a project and a path in
the project no longer exists, it will not be added to the listtree

The string gadget below should it contain either a valid image path or
valid PhotoFolio Listtree project file.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Add one/all/recursively@{ub}

This determines the way the default path will be added to the listtree and
it is only valid for a image path, not a Listtree project.
@{PARD}


@{b}@{i}Miscellaneous@{ub}@{ui}



@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Safety memory limit@{ub}

If the amount of free memory goes below this setting during a load,
PhotoFolio will stop the load and display pagination gadgets. This should
be set at about 2.5M to allow space for image displaying.

@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Photoalbum compatability@{ub}

With this turned on, PhotoFolio will automatically recognise Photoalbum
thumbnails and display them in the @{"browse window" Link "Browse_window"}.

@{b}@{i}Note@{ub}@{ui} Photoalbum thumbnails cannot have their attributes
set.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Confirm quit@{ub}

With this turned on, a requester will pop up requesting confirmation to quit.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Automatic error window@{ub}

With this turned on, the @{"error window" Link "Error_window" } will
automatically open, or if it is already open, be brought to the front,
whenever an error occurs. If it is turned off, errors will still be added
to the window, but it will not be opened automatically.

@{PARD}

@EndNode

@Node "VLab_window" "PhotoFolio.guide/VLab_window"
@Prev "Windows"

@Smartwrap

@{b}@{u}VLab Window@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}@{i}Note@{ub}@{ui} To use this option, you must have a VLab card @{b}AND@{ub} VLab.mcc


	This window gives you access to the VLab card. Here you can grab images and send them to a @{"browse window" Link "Browse_window" }.
The window has 4 buttons:


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Monitor on/off@{ub}

This displays a greyscale monitor in the top of the VLab window. The speed
the monitor updates depends on how busy your system is and how fast your
CPU is.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Grab@{ub}

This grabs an image from the VLab card and sends it to the @{"browse window" Link "Browse_window" }.
This can be slow and it depends on your settings. For the fastest possible
grab, turn VMem OFF in the VLab prefs in the MUI settings requester. Of
course you will need to have enough available memory to do this. Either
way, the conversion process from YUV to RGB is slow and don't expect it to
happen very fast.

Once the image is sent to the browse window, you can show it (scaling is
disabled), delete it or save it. If you select Save Proof or Save Selected
Proofs, PhotoFolio automatically detects that it is a VLab image and saves
the image before it saves the proof. Once saved, the image is a normal
proof and will operate like any other. The image is saved as a JPeg.

@{PARD}

@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Quick Grab@{ub}

Due to the slow speed of the Grab function, I have added this Quick Grab
option. With this an image is grabbed from the VLab card, however no YUV
conversions are performed and the image is not sent to the @{"browse window" Link "Browse_window" }.
The image is stored internally and when you have done your grabbing, use
Build Grab to send the grabbed images to the @{"browse window" Link "Browse_window" }.
If VMem is turned on in the VLab.mcc, this uses very little memory. A
counter to the right displays the number of grabs currently stored.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Build Grab@{ub}

This is used to send the stored grabs to the @{"browse window" Link "Browse_window" }.
This is the slow part of the process, so if you have grabbed a lot of images, have a
coffee! Currently the build process cannot be aborted. Each time an image
is built the counter on the right decrements.
@{PARD}

@EndNode

@Node "Move_window" "PhotoFolio.guide/Move_window"
@Prev "Windows"

@Smartwrap

@{b}@{u}Move Window@{ub}@{uu}


This window allows you to enter the paths and select the move mode you want
to use.


Please note that once a move has been started, you cannot stop it until it
is finished.


There are several rules when moving proofs and images, they are as follows:


	· The proof destination path @{b}cannot@{ub} match the current proof path.


	· The images destination path @{b}cannot@{ub} match the current image path.


	· If the proofs are linked, the proof destination path @{b}cannot@{ub} match the
image destination path.


	· An image destinaton path @{b}must@{ub} be supplied.


	· A proof destinaton path is optional depending on whether the proof is
linked or non-linked.


	· If the proofs are non-linked the proof destination path will be ignored
and the proofs will stay with the image.


	· If you have selected move proofs only, and PhotoFolio encounters a
non-linked proof, it will @{b}NOT@{ub} be moved and the @{"error window" Link "Error_window" }
will be opened displaying the error.


	· If you have selected move proofs only, and PhotoFolio encounters a unsaved proof
it will @{b}NOT@{ub} be moved and the @{"error window" Link "Error_window" } will be opened
displaying the error.


	· When you move only the image, the associated proof will be
automatically re-targeted to point to the new location.


	· If a linked proof of the same name already already exists in the
destination path, the proof will not be moved and the @{"error window" Link "Error_window" } will be
opened displaying the error.


	· If a image of the same name already exists in the destination path, a
requester will open asking you if you want to overwrite it. If you say
"Yes" or "Yes to All" the linked proof associated with that image will also
be overwritten (if one exists).


	· If a non-linked proof of the same name already already exists in the
destination path, the proof will be moved and renamed.


	· If a linked proof is moved to a new path, it will be removed from the
current @{"browse window" Link "Browse_window" }.


The window has several options:


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Move proofs@{ub}

Check this if you want to move proofs.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Proof destination directory@{ub}

This is the path you want to move the proofs to.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Move images@{ub}

Check this if you want to move images
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Image destination directory@{ub}

This is the path you want to move the images to.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Move@{ub}

This commences the move function.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Cancel@{ub}

This aborts the move operation.
@{PARD}


@EndNode

@Node "MysticView_window" "PhotoFolio.guide/MysticView_window"
@Prev "Windows"

@Smartwrap

@{u}@{b}MysticView window@{uu}@{ub}


@{" MysticView Main Menu " Link "MysticView_main_menu" }


PhotoFolio  supports @{"MysticView" Link "MysticView" } internally. Use the
@{"settings window" Link "Settings_window" } to set up the internal default
viewer  for PhotoFolio. Settings for @{"MysticView" Link "MysticView" } can
also be adjusted here.


If you have "Show Buttons" checked, the top of the window will contain a
button bar, these buttons control the viewer. The button bar can be turned
on and off from the @{"MysticView main menu" Link "MysticView_main_menu" }.


The buttons in the button bar are as follows:


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}First@{ub}

If more than one image was selected, this takes you to the first image.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Previous@{ub}

If more than one image was selected, this takes you to the previous image.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Next@{ub}

If more than one image was selected, this takes you to the next image.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Display 1:1 Pixel/Scale with Aspect@{ub}

Scale with Aspect means that the image is scaled to fit the window size,
maintaining its aspect ratio. If the window is re-sized, the image will
also be re-sized.

Display 1:1 Pixel means the image is displayed actual size, regardless of
the window size.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Reset all@{ub}

This resets the move, rotation and zoom values to their default settings.
@{PARD}


Below the button bar is the image. If "Show Picture Info" is checked, then
below the image is an image information line which can be turned on and
off. It displays the image file name and the size of the image (width x
height).

@EndNode

@Node "MysticView_main_menu" "PhotoFolio.guide/MysticView_main_menu"
@Prev "MysticView_window"

@Smartwrap

@{u}@{b}MysticView Main Menu@{uu}@{ub}


Right clicking on a MysticView window will give you access to these menu options.


@{u}Picture@{uu}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Next@{ub}

If more than one image was selected, this takes you to the next image.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Previous@{ub}

If more than one image was selected, this takes you to the previous image.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}First@{ub}

If more than one image was selected, this takes you to the first image.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Move@{ub}
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
			@{b}Left@{ub}

		This will scroll the image left.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
			@{b}Right@{ub}

		This will scroll the image right.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
			@{b}Up@{ub}

		This will scroll the image up.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
			@{b}Down@{ub}

		This will scroll the image down.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
			@{b}Center@{ub}

		This will center the image in the window.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Zoom@{ub}
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
			@{b}Zoom In@{ub}

		This will zoom the image in.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
			@{b}Zoom Out@{ub}

		This will zoom the image out.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
			@{b}Reset Zoom@{ub}

		This will reset the zoom to normal.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Rotate@{ub}
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
			@{b}Rotate Left@{ub}

		This will rotate the image left 30 degrees.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
			@{b}Rotate Right@{ub}

		This will rotate the image right 30 degrees.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
			@{b}Reset Rotate@{ub}

		This will reset the rotate to normal.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Reset All@{ub}

This will reset the move/rotate/zoom setings to normal.
@{PARD}


@{u}Options@{uu}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Scale with Aspect@{ub}

Scale with Aspect means that the image is scaled to fit the window size,
maintaining its aspect ratio. If the window is re-sized, the image will
also be re-sized.This mode guarantees that the image is always fully
visible.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Display 1:1 Pixel@{ub}

Display 1:1 Pixel means the image is displayed actual size, regardless of
the window size. Represent each pixel in the image by one pixel on the
screen.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Show Buttons@{ub}

This turns the button bar in the top of the MysticView window on and off.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Show Picture Info@{ub}

This turns the picture information bar in the bottom of the MysticView
window on and off. It displays the image file name and the size of the
image (width x height).
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Show Arrows@{ub}

When enabled, draw arrows at the picture's borders, when it is not fully
visible in the respective direction.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Show PIP@{ub}

This displays a thumbnail of the image in the top left hand corner of the
image. It contains a green box which indicates the visible portion of the
image.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Show Cursor@{ub}

This setting will activate a tiny crosshair on the picture, indicating the
current cursor position. scrolling will move the cursor, and zooming will
go to that destination.
@{PARD}


@{LINDENT 6}
	@{b}Mouse Drag Image@{ub}

This enable scrolling of an image by clicking the left button and dragging
the mouse.
@{PARD}

@EndNode
